 Let x be the height of the figure after folding. The similarity of the triangles gives the relations x^2 = ED = 36x - x^3. The solution to this is x = 6 (as x= 0 doesn't make sense). <answer>  656 \end{amslatex} 

Let $x$ be the height of the figure after folding. The similarity of the triangles gives the relations $x^2 = ED = 7x - x^3$. Solving the cubic equation $x^3 + x^2 - 7x = 0$, we obtain $x = 6$ (neglecting the $x = 0$ solution as it does not make sense mathematically).

Hence, the solution is $b + c + d = 6 + 3 + 7 = \boxed{16}$.

